      "explanation": "Type II usually presents in childhood with bilirubin levels between 6-20 mg/dL, which is higher than this patient's level of 3 mg/dL."
    },
    {
      "claim": "Gilbert syndrome is a benign, hereditary condition causing mild unconjugated hyperbilirubinemia.",
      "label": "factual",
      "explanation": "This is the standard definition of Gilbert syndrome, characterized by a mild, often intermittent elevation in unconjugated bilirubin."
    },
    {
      "claim": "Gilbert syndrome often first becomes noticeable around puberty.",
      "label": "factual",
      "explanation": "The reduced UGT1A1 activity in Gilbert syndrome is often unmasked after puberty, making presentation in adolescence common."
